modules.description: Performs elliptic curve operations for ECDH key exchange using the P-256 curve, including point multiplication and scalar operations. Works with cryptographic scalars and elliptic curve points represented as byte arrays. Used to generate shared secrets and manage private/public key pairs in cryptographic protocols.

Provides functions for generating Ephemeral Diffie-Hellman key pairs and performing key exchanges using the P256 elliptic curve. Operates on secret keys and Cstruct.t for public keys, ensuring valid curve points and proper encoding. Used to establish shared secrets in secure communication protocols where ephemeral keys are required.
